obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34852)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34852&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Khuda Bakhsh Oriental Public`
  line `Library Act, 1969.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 21st July, 1970, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1255(E), dated 17th July, 1970, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i)/`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34853)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration of Khuda Bakhsh Oriental Public Library as an institution of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34853&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that the Khuda Bakhsh Oriental Public Library at Patna in the State of`
  line `Bihar is an institution of national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34854)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34854&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Board established under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) "deed of trust" means the deed of trust No. 217 executed in the office of the Deputy Registrar`
  line `of Patna by the late Maulvi Khuda Bakhsh Khan Bahadur of Muradpur on the 14th January, 1891;`
  line
  line `(d) "Fund" means the Fund referred to in section 19;`
  line
  line `(e) "library" means the Khuda Bakhsh Oriental Public Library declared to be an institution of`
  line `national importance under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "member" means a member of the Board and includes the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "State Government" means the Government of Bihar.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34855)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34855&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be established for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, a Board to be known as the Khuda Bakhsh Oriental Public Library Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property`
  line `and contract, and may, by that name, sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34856)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Composition of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34856&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall consist of the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Governor of Bihar, ex officio, Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) the Accountant General, Bihar, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) a person to be nominated by the Central Government, who shall be a member of the family of`
  line `the late Maulvi Khuda Bakhsh Khan Bahadur of Muradpur;`
  line
  line `(d) eight persons, four each to be nominated by the Central Government and the State`
  line `Government, who shall, as far as possible, be persons having knowledge of, and experience in,`
  line `matters relating to the administration of libraries;`
  line
  line `(e) the Director, Khuda Bakhsh Oriental Public Library, ex officio Member-Secretary.`
  line
  line `(2) Every nomination under this section shall take effect as soon as it is notified by the Central`
  line `Government in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34857)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office and fresh nomination in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34857&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The terms of office of nominated`
  line `members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any nominated member may resign his office by giving notice in writing to the Central`
  line `Government and to the State Government, and on such resignation being notified by the Central`
  line `Government, in the Official Gazette shall be deemed to have vacated his office.`
  line
  line `(3) A casual vacancy created by the resignation of a nominated member under sub-section (2) or for`
  line `any other reason may be filled by fresh nomination by the Central Government or the State Government,`
  line `as the case may be, and a member so nominated shall hold office for the remaining period for which the`
  line `member in whose place he is nominated would have held office.`
  line
  line `(4) An outgoing member shall be eligible for renomination.`
  line
  line `(5) If any nominated member is by infirmity or otherwise rendered temporarily incapable of carrying`
  line `out his duties or is absent on leave or otherwise in circumstances not involving the vacation of his office,`
  line `the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, may nominate another person to act`
  line `in his place during his absence.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34879)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34879&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No act of the Board shall be invalid merely by reason`
  line of--
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Board, or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the nomination of a person acting as a member thereof, or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34880)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Duty of Government nominating persons, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34880&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before nominating a person to be a member`
  line `of the Board, the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, shall satisfy itself that`
  line `the person will have no such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially the exercise or`
  line `performance by him of his functions as a member, and the Central Government or the State Government,`
  line `as the case may be, shall also satisfy itself from time to time with respect to every member nominated by`
  line `it that he has no such interest; and any person who is or whom the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, proposes to nominate and who has consented to be, a member shall,`
  line `whenever requested by the Central Government or the State Government so to do, furnish to it such`
  line `information as that Government considers necessary for the performance by it of its duties under this`
  line sub-section.
  line
  line `(2) A nominated member who is in any way, directly or indirectly, interested in a contract made or`
  line `proposed to be made, by the Board shall, as soon as possible, after relevant circumstances have come to`
  line `his knowledge, disclose the nature of his interest at a meeting of the Board and the disclosure shall be`
  line `recorded in the minutes of the Board and the member shall not take any part after the disclosure in any`
  line `deliberation or decision of the Board with respect to that contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34859)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34859&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-sections (2), (3) and (4), observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of`
  line `business at its meetings (including the quorum at meetings) as may be provided by regulations made`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman or, in his absence, any member chosen by the members present from among`
  line `themselves, shall preside at a meeting of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) If any nominated member, being an officer of Government, is unable to attend any meeting of the`
  line `Board, he may, with the previous approval of the Chairman, authorise any person in writing to do so.`
  line
  line `(4) All questions at a meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority of the votes of the members`
  line `present and voting and in the case of an equality of votes, the Chairman or, in his absence the member`
  line `presiding, shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34860)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Temporary association of persons with Board for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34860&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may`
  line `associate with itself in such manner and for such purposes as may be provided by regulations made under`
  line `this Act, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire in performing any of its functions under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) A person associated with it by the Board under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall have the right`
  line `to take part in the discussions of the Board relating to that purpose, but shall not, by virtue of this section,`
  line `be entitled to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (34861)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34861&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of the`
  line `Board shall be authenticated by the signature of the Chairman or any other member authorised by the`
  line `Board in this behalf, and all other instruments issued by the Board shall be authenticated by the signature`
  line `of an officer of the Board authorised in like manner in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (34862)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Staff of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34862&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the Board may, for the purpose`
  line `of enabling it efficiently to perform its functions under this Act, appoint such number of officers and other`
  line `employees as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The recruitment and conditions of service of such officers and employees shall be such as may be`
  line `provided by regulations made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (34863)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Transfer of service of existing employees to Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34863&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `every person employed in the library immediately before the date of establishment of the Board shall, on`
  line `and from such date, become an employee of the Board with such designation as the Board may determine`
  line `and shall hold his office or service therein by the same tenure, at the same remuneration and upon the`
  line `same terms and conditions as he would have held the same on such date if the Board had not been`
  line `established and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment in the Board is terminated or until`
  line `such tenure, remuneration and terms and conditions are duly altered by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that the tenure, remuneration and terms and conditions of service of any such person shall`
  line `not be altered to his disadvantage without the previous approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (34864)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Location of library.`
  content `The library shall be located at Patna.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34864&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (34865)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Property and liabilities of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34865&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the establishment of the Board--`
  line
  line `(i) all properties, funds and dues which are vested in, or realisable by, the trustees of the library`
  line `constituted by the deed of trust, in their capacity as such, shall vest in, and be realisable by; the`
  line `Board; and`
  line
  line `(ii) all liabilities in relation to the library which are enforceable against the said trustees, shall be`
  line `enforceable only against the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) All properties, which may, after the establishment of the Board, be given, bequeathed or otherwise`
  line `transferred to the library or acquired by the Board, shall vest in the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (34866)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Duties of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34866&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of the deed of trust, it shall be the general duty of`
  line `the Board to manage the library and to plan, promote, organise and implement programmes for the`
  line `development of the library on modern scientific lines (including the microfilming of rare manuscripts)`
  line `and to perform such other functions as the Central Government may, from time to time, assign to the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, the Board may`
  line `take such steps as it thinks fit--`
  line
  line `(a) for providing for instruction and research in matters relating to libraries and for the`
  line `advancement of learning and dissemination of knowledge in such matters; and`
  line
  line `(b) to do all such other things as may be necessary for the discharge of its functions under this`
  line Act..
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (34867)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34867&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions and restrictions as the Central Government`
  line `may think fit to impose, the Board may exercise all such powers as may be necessary or expedient for the`
  line `purpose of carrying out its duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such regulations as may be made by the Board in this behalf, the Board may from time`
  line `to time purchase or otherwise acquire such manuscripts, books, articles or things as may, in the opinion of`
  line `the Board, be worthy of preservation in the library.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (34868)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Grants by Central Government to Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34868&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling the Board to discharge`
  line `its functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Board in each financial year such sums of money as that`
  line `Government considers necessary by way of grant, loan or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (34869)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Fund of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34869&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain a Fund to which shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys paid by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) such sums of money as the State Government may pay annually having regard to its resolution`
  line `No. V/L 4055/60E 120, dated the 26th September, 1962;`
  line
  line `(c) all fees and other charges levied under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) all moneys received by the Board by way of grant, gift, donation, benefaction, bequest,`
  line `subscription, contribution or transfer;`
  line
  line `(e) all other moneys received by the Board in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may expend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this Act and`
  line `such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) A sum of money not exceeding such amount as may be provided by regulations made under this`
  line `Act may be kept in current account with any scheduled bank as defined in section 2 of the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), or any other bank approved by the Central Government in this behalf, but`
  line `any moneys in excess of that sum shall be deposited in the Reserve Bank of India or with the agents of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India or invested in such manner as may be approved by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (34870)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34870&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall, by such date in each year as may be specified by the Central`
  line `Government, submit to it for approval a budget for the next financial year in the form specified by it,`
  line `showing the estimated receipts and expenditure, and the sums which would be required from the Central`
  line `Government during that financial year.`
  line
  line `(2) If any sum granted by the Central Government remains wholly or partly unspent in any financial`
  line `year, the unspent sum may be carried forward to the next financial year and taken into account in`
  line `determining the sum to be provided by the Central Government for that year.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), no sum shall be expended by or on behalf of the`
  line `Board, unless the expenditure is covered by provision in the budget approved by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to such conditions and restrictions as the Central Government may think fit to impose, the`
  line `Board may sanction any reappropriation from one head of expenditure to another or from a provision`
  line `made for one purpose to that for another purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (34871)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34871&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the balance-sheet in such form as may be`
  line `specified, and in accordance with such general directions as may be issued by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Board to`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Board shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books,`
  line `accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the office of the Board, and`
  line `the library.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (34872)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Returns and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34872&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall furnish to the Central Government at such time and`
  line `in such form and in such manner as the Central Government may direct such returns, statements and`
  line `particulars as the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1) the Board shall, as soon as possible after the`
  line `commencement of each financial year, submit to the Central Government within such time as may be`
  line `specified by the Central Government a report giving true and full account of the activities of the Board`
  line `during the previous financial year and an account of activities likely to be undertaken during the current`
  line `financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (34873)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions to Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34873&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the discharge of its`
  line `functions under this Act, the Board shall be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central`
  line `Government may give to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall be given an opportunity to express its views before any direction is`
  line `given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (34874)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Delegation of powers and duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34874&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by general or special order in writing, direct`
  line `that all or any of the powers or duties which may be exercised or discharged by it shall, in such`
  line `circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order, be exercised or`
  line `discharged also by any member, officer or employee of the Board specified in this behalf in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (34875)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Officers and employees of Board to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34875&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `All officers and employees of the`
  line `Board shall, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or`
  line `regulation made thereunder, be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (34876)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34876&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Board or any member, officer or employee of the Board for any thing which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rule or regulation made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (34877)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 1981, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 24-12-1981).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34877&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that when the Board has been established, no such rules shall be made without consulting`
  line `the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, the members`
  line `nominated under clauses (c) and (d) of sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the travelling and other allowances payable to a member other than the Chairman and to a`
  line `person associated with the Board under section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) the disqualifications for membership of the Board and the procedure to be followed in`
  line `removing a member who is or becomes subject to any disqualification;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions subject to which, and the mode in which, contracts may be entered into by or`
  line `on behalf of the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which has to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session ^1`
  line `[or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid] both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (34878)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power of Board to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1981, s. 3 (w.e.f. 24-12-1981)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568&sectionId=34878&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00011_196943_1517807324568
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations not inconsistent with this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder, for enabling it to discharge its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions and restrictions subject to which manuscripts and books in the library may be`
  line used;
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which, and the purposes for which, persons may be associated with the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the time and place of meetings of the Board, the procedure to be followed in regard to the`
  line `transaction of business at such meetings and the quorum necessary for the transaction of business at a`
  line meeting;
  line
  line `(d) the maintenance of minutes of meetings of the Board and the transmission of copies thereof to`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) the recruitment and conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Board;`
  line
  line `(f) the persons by whom and the manner in which, payments, deposits and investments may be`
  line `made on behalf of the Board;`
  line
  line `(g) the maximum amount that may be kept in the current account;`
  line
  line `(h) the maintenance of registers and accounts;`
  line
  line `(i) the compilation of catalogues and inventories of the manuscripts, books and other articles and`
  line `things in the library;`
  line
  line `(j) the steps to be taken for the preservation of the manuscripts, books and other articles and`
  line `things in the library;`
  line
  line `(k) the general management of the library;`
  line
  line `(l) the fees and other charges to be levied for the use of manuscripts and books in the library;`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter in respect of which provision is, in the opinion of the Board, necessary for`
  line `the performance of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, after consultation with the Board, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, amend, vary or rescind any regulation which it has approved; and thereupon the regulation shall`
  line `have effect accordingly, but without prejudice to the exercise of the powers of the Board under`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2).`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(4) Every regulation made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
